@startuml rrwm-loop
' RRWM online weighted-majority update loop (Cortes et al. 2015, Fig. 6).
' Each round: predict by sampling Wₜ₋₁, observe a loss transducer Vₜ, compose,
' weight-push to restore a stochastic automaton. Deep-learning purple for the
' learner; algorithms-green for the WFST ops it drives. Palette: docs/diagrams/README.md.
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam ArrowColor #607D8B
skinparam ArrowThickness 1.3
skinparam activity {
  BackgroundColor #E1BEE7
  BorderColor #6A1B9A
  FontColor #102027
  DiamondBackgroundColor #FFF59D
  DiamondBorderColor #F9A825
  DiamondFontColor #5D4037
}

title <b>RRWM online learning loop</b>\n<size:11><i>cumulative automaton <latex>W_t</latex> over the <latex>\eta</latex>-power semiring; regret <latex>E[R_T] \le 2M\sqrt{T \log N}</latex></i></size>

start
:**<latex>W_0</latex>** ← one-state automaton\n(all paths weight <latex>\bar{1}</latex>);
repeat
  #E1BEE7:**predict** <latex>\hat{y}_t \sim W_{t-1}</latex>\n(sample <latex>\propto</latex> weight);
  :observe outcome <latex>y_t</latex>\nbuild loss transducer **<latex>V_t</latex>**;
  #C8E6C9:**compose**  <latex>W_t</latex> ← <latex>W_{t-1} \circ V_t</latex>\n(combine all path experts);
  #C8E6C9:**weight-push**  <latex>W_t</latex> ← push(<latex>W_t</latex>)\n(restore stochastic: out-weights sum to <latex>\bar{1}</latex>);
  :accumulate loss <latex>\ell(\hat{y}_t, y_t)</latex>;
repeat while (round < T  and  states < max_rounds?) is (yes)
->no\n(reset <latex>W_t</latex> ← <latex>W_0</latex> if cap hit);
:return <latex>W_T</latex>\n(learned expert weighting);
stop

legend right
  | Step | Operation |
  |<#E1BEE7> predict | sample path from <latex>W_{t-1}</latex> |
  | observe | construct <latex>V_t</latex> from loss |
  |<#C8E6C9> compose | <latex>W_{t-1} \circ V_t</latex> |
  |<#C8E6C9> push | make stochastic for next sample |
endlegend
@enduml
